abstract: The formal notification to Congress prompted bipartisan outcry and accusations that the administration had again overstepped its constitutional authority.
snippet: The formal notification to Congress prompted bipartisan outcry and accusations that the administration had again overstepped its constitutional authority.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Pentagon plans to divert $3.8 billion intended for military equipment to the construction of a wall at the southwestern border, it informed lawmakers on Thursday, drawing bipartisan outrage and reviving a long-running battle with Congress over funding for President Trump’s signature campaign promise.

abstract: The decision to restore charges against Jussie Smollett could bedevil the reelection bid of the first black woman to hold Chicago's top law enforcement job and potentially alter the trajectory of a prosecutor once seen as a rising star in Illinois politics.
snippet: The decision to restore charges against Jussie Smollett could bedevil the reelection bid of the first black woman to hold Chicago's top law enforcement job and potentially alter the trajectory of a prosecutor once seen as a rising star in Illinois...
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — The decision to restore charges against Jussie Smollett could bedevil the reelection bid of the first black woman to hold Chicago's top law enforcement job and potentially alter the trajectory of a prosecutor once seen as a rising star in Illinois politics.
headline_main: Smollett Case Could Complicate Reelection of Top Prosecutor
headline_print_headline: Smollett Case Could Complicate Reelection of Top Prosecutor

abstract: The top judge on the U.S. District Court in Washington said in an unusual public statement on Thursday that public criticism "is not a factor" in sentencing decisions, after President Donald Trump took aim at a judge from her court who is overseeing longtime Trump adviser Roger Stone's criminal trial.
snippet: The top judge on the U.S. District Court in Washington said in an unusual public statement on Thursday that public criticism "is not a factor" in sentencing decisions, after President Donald Trump took aim at a judge from her court who is overseei...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The top judge on the U.S. District Court in Washington said in an unusual public statement on Thursday that public criticism "is not a factor" in sentencing decisions, after President Donald Trump took aim at a judge from her court who is overseeing longtime Trump adviser Roger Stone's criminal trial.
headline_main: Senior U.S. Judge Defends Sentencing Decisions After Trump Tweet on Stone Case
headline_print_headline: Senior U.S. Judge Defends Sentencing Decisions After Trump Tweet on Stone Case

abstract: The European Union says it is donating 4 million euros ($4.3 million) to help refugees in Mexico, Costa Rica and Honduras find living-wage jobs and better integrate into society.
snippet: The European Union says it is donating 4 million euros ($4.3 million) to help refugees in Mexico, Costa Rica and Honduras find living-wage jobs and better integrate into society.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — The European Union says it is donating 4 million euros ($4.3 million) to help refugees in Mexico, Costa Rica and Honduras find living-wage jobs and better integrate into society.
headline_main: EU, Others Work on Refugee Job Development in Latin America
headline_print_headline: EU, Others Work on Refugee Job Development in Latin America

abstract: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson has postponed a trip to the United States to meet U.S. President Donald Trump so he can stay at home to focus on delivering his domestic agenda, the Sun newspaper reported late on Thursday.
snippet: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson has postponed a trip to the United States to meet U.S. President Donald Trump so he can stay at home to focus on delivering his domestic agenda, the Sun newspaper reported late on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - British Prime Minister Boris Johnson has postponed a trip to the United States to meet U.S. President Donald Trump so he can stay at home to focus on delivering his domestic agenda, the Sun newspaper reported late on Thursday.
headline_main: UK PM Johnson's Meeting With Trump Postponed Until June: The Sun
headline_print_headline: UK PM Johnson's Meeting With Trump Postponed Until June: The Sun

abstract: A meeting between U.S. President Donald Trump and New York Governor Andrew Cuomo on immigration policies and a travel program was productive, with discussions set to continue, the acting Department of Homeland Security chief said on Thursday.
snippet: A meeting between U.S. President Donald Trump and New York Governor Andrew Cuomo on immigration policies and a travel program was productive, with discussions set to continue, the acting Department of Homeland Security chief said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A meeting between U.S. President Donald Trump and New York Governor Andrew Cuomo on immigration policies and a travel program was productive, with discussions set to continue, the acting Department of Homeland Security chief said on Thursday.
headline_main: Trump, New York's Cuomo Will Continue Talks on Immigration, Traveler Program: Official
headline_print_headline: Trump, New York's Cuomo Will Continue Talks on Immigration, Traveler Program: Official

abstract: President Donald Trump on Thursday appointed one of Republican Senator Ted Cruz's former staffers to lead a Justice Department office at the heart of a recent whistleblower complaint over anti-human trafficking grants awarded in 2019.
snippet: President Donald Trump on Thursday appointed one of Republican Senator Ted Cruz's former staffers to lead a Justice Department office at the heart of a recent whistleblower complaint over anti-human trafficking grants awarded in 2019.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump on Thursday appointed one of Republican Senator Ted Cruz's former staffers to lead a Justice Department office at the heart of a recent whistleblower complaint over anti-human trafficking grants awarded in 2019.
headline_main: Trump Taps New Director of Grants Office That Gave Awards to Hookers for Jesus
headline_print_headline: Trump Taps New Director of Grants Office That Gave Awards to Hookers for Jesus

abstract: The decision dealt a blow to Joe Biden, who had hoped his longstanding ties to organized labor would win him the union’s coveted support.
snippet: The decision dealt a blow to Joe Biden, who had hoped his longstanding ties to organized labor would win him the union’s coveted support.
lead_paragraph: A powerful union in Nevada declined to endorse a candidate in the Democratic primary, dealing a blow to former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., who had hoped his longstanding ties to organized labor and opposition to “Medicare for all” would win him its support and a much-needed boost in the state’s upcoming caucuses.

abstract: Conservative talk show host Rush Limbaugh drew bipartisan criticism Thursday for saying the country won't elect Pete Buttigieg president because he's been “kissing his husband" on stage after debates.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Conservative talk show host Rush Limbaugh drew bipartisan criticism Thursday for saying the country won't elect Pete Buttigieg president because he's been “kissing his husband" on stage after debates.
